{% extends "partials/_master.jinja" %}

{% block title %}About{% endblock %}

{% block content %}
<article>
	<section>
		<h1>About Winter91</h1>
		<p>The challenge that keeps you moving through winter</p>
	</section>
	
	<section>
		<h2>What is Winter91?</h2>
		<p>
			Winter91 is a fitness challenge designed to help you stay active during the winter months. 
			The goal is simple: walk or run 91 miles (one for every day of winter) between the start of winter and the end of the challenge period.
		</p>
		
		<blockquote>
			"Above all, do not lose your desire to walk. Everyday, I walk myself into a state of well-being 
			and walk away from every illness. I have walked myself into my best thoughts, and I know of no 
			thought so burdensome that one cannot walk away from it."
			<cite>SÃ¸ren Kierkegaard</cite>
		</blockquote>
	</section>
	
	<section>
		<h2>How It Works</h2>
		<ol>
			<li><strong>Sign Up:</strong> Get an invitation code and create your account</li>
			<li><strong>Log Miles:</strong> Track your daily walks and runs</li>
			<li><strong>Stay Motivated:</strong> Watch your progress and compete on the leaderboard</li>
			<li><strong>Reach 91:</strong> Complete the challenge by hitting 91 miles!</li>
		</ol>
	</section>
	
	<section>
		<h2>Challenge Rules</h2>
		<ul>
			<li>Any outdoor walking or running counts toward your total</li>
			<li>Indoor activities like treadmills count too</li>
			<li>Log your miles honestly - this is about personal growth</li>
			<li>Stay consistent and build healthy habits</li>
			<li>Support and encourage your fellow challengers</li>
		</ul>
	</section>
	
	<section>
		<h2>Why Winter?</h2>
		<p>
			Winter is often the most challenging time to stay active. The days are shorter,
			the weather is harsh, and motivation can be hard to find. Winter 91 provides
			structure, accountability, and community to help you not just survive winter,
			but thrive through it.
		</p>
		
		<p>
			By the end of the challenge, you'll have built lasting habits, improved your
			fitness, and proven to yourself that you can stay committed even when things get tough.
		</p>
	</section>
	
  <hr/>
	<div style="text-align: center; margin-top: 3rem;">
		{% if walker_id.isNone() %}
			<a href="/signup" role="button">Join the Challenge</a>
		{% else %}
			<a href="/log" role="button">Log Your Miles</a>
		{% endif %}
	</div>
</article>
{% endblock %}
